Q: State few applications of Machine Learning.
   [Asked in: P2-1a]

  1. Email Spam Filtering: Machine learning algorithms (like Naive Bayes, SVM) analyze
     email content, subject lines, sender patterns, and metadata to automatically
     classify incoming emails as spam or legitimate (ham).

  2. Financial Fraud Detection: Banks and credit card companies use ML models to scan
     millions of transactions in real-time, identifying unusual patterns (sudden large
     transactions, purchases in unfamiliar locations) and flagging them as potentially
     fraudulent.

  3. Medical Diagnosis and Healthcare: ML models analyze medical images (X-rays, MRIs,
     CT scans) to detect diseases like cancer, diabetic retinopathy, and pneumonia.
     They can also predict patient readmission risk and recommend personalized
     treatment plans.

  4. Recommendation Systems: Platforms like Netflix, Amazon, YouTube, and Spotify use
     collaborative filtering and content-based filtering ML algorithms to recommend
     movies, products, videos, and songs tailored to individual user preferences and
     browsing history.

  5. Self-Driving Cars: Autonomous vehicles use deep learning models for real-time
     object detection, lane detection, pedestrian recognition, and decision-making
     while navigating roads.

  6. Natural Language Processing (NLP): ML powers virtual assistants (Siri, Alexa,
     Google Assistant), language translation services (Google Translate), chatbots,
     sentiment analysis of customer reviews, and text summarization.


